quote: One more thing...
author: Steve Jobs

quote: I know a thing or two about love. Well, maybe just a thing. A big, blurry thing, like Bigfoot.
author: Jarod Kintz,  Love quotes for the ages. Specifically ages 18-81.

quote: You are the most important thing to me now. The most important thing to me ever.
author: Stephenie Meyer,  Twilight

quote: I do not know everything; still many things I understand.
author: Madeleine L'Engle,  A Wrinkle in Time

quote: I am one thing, my writings are another.
author: Friedrich Nietzsche

quote: Object of Desire A woman knows she's the object of a unknown man's desirelike a game animal becoming aware it is being looked at.
author: Beryl Dov

quote: Stuff your brain with knowledge.
author: Karl Lagerfeld

quote: A human being - what is a human being? Everything and nothing. Through the power of thought it can mirror everything it experiences. Through memory and knowledge it becomes a microcosm, carrying the world within itself. A mirror of things, a mirror of facts. Each human being becomes a little universe within the universe!
author: Guy de Maupassant

quote: The things that we love tell us what we are.
author: Thomas Aquinas

quote: The things we love destroy us every time, lad. Remember that.
author: George R.R. Martin,  A Game of Thrones

quote: I only know that I know nothing
author: Socrates

quote: Sometimes a symbol holds more power than the thing it represents. Like the symbol for Thing, the one I created that is confusing and abstract and makes people ask, What is that thing? And I always reply, “If you already knew, why did you ask?
author: Jarod Kintz,  This Book is Not FOR SALE

quote: Something deeply hidden had to be behind things.
author: Albert Einstein,  Autobiographical Notes

quote: Big things begin with big thinking.
author: Kent Healy

quote: Ideas come from everything
author: Alfred Hitchcock

quote: Ideas are the source of all things
author: Plato

quote: For me an object is something living. This cigarette or this box of matches contains a secret life much more intense than that of certain human beings.
author: Joan Miro

quote: You don’t know anything, but I know even less.
author: Dejan Stojanovic,  The Sun Watches the Sun

quote: A joke's a very serious thing.
author: Charles Churchill

quote: Look up.
author: Luanne Rice,  Silver Bells

quote: The knowledge of all things is possible
author: Leonardo da Vinci

quote: Things always become obvious after the fact
author: Nassim Nicholas Taleb

quote: I'm not young enough to know everything.
author: J.M. Barrie,  The Admirable Crichton

quote: Since we cannot know all there is to be known about anything, we ought to know a little about everything.
author: Blaise Pascal

quote: Laters, baby.
author: E.L. James,  Fifty Shades of Grey

quote: We love the things we love for what they are.
author: Robert Frost

quote: The basic idea is that all things in the universe are intertwined.
author: Stephen Richards,  Cosmic Ordering Guide

quote: Imagination is Everything!
author: Termina Ashton

quote: What we think, we become
author: Buddha

quote: I am not young enough to know everything.
author: Oscar Wilde

quote: You must do the things you think you cannot do.
author: Eleanor Roosevelt

quote: When someone looks at something they don’t understand and they say, “That could be a good thing, or that could be a bad thing,” they’re just highlighting the fact that they have no clue what they are talking about. Everything in the universe, besides God, could be a good or bad thing.
author: Jarod Kintz,  This Book Has No Title

quote: Gimme an S! A T! An O! A C! Followed by a K-H-O-L-M! What's it spell? HEAD FUCK.- Jane
author: J.R. Ward,  Lover Unbound

quote: We can never know what might have been but what is to come is another matter entirely
author: C.S. Lewis

quote: Nothing is as it seems, but something is everything it is made out to be.
author: Carroll Bryant

quote: All that I've learned, I've forgotten. The little that I still know, I've guessed.
author: Nicolas Chamfort

quote: If you don't know everything, you must go on with what you do know.
author: Robert Jordan,  A Crown of Swords

quote: Silly String [10w] Life' an absurdity radiating from a spine of silly string.
author: Beryl Dov

quote: I love all things, not only the grand but the infinitely small: thimble, spurs, plates, flower vases.....
author: Pablo Neruda

quote: A little perspective, like a little humor, goes a long way.
author: Allen Klein

quote: The bat is not a toy, it's a weapon. It gives me everything in life, which helps me to do everything on the field.
author: Virat Kohli

quote: It's all in the mind.
author: George Harrison

quote: No man is ever just one thing.
author: Michael Scott,  The Enchantress

quote: You matter.
author: Suzanne Young,  The Treatment

quote: Somebody knows.
author: Ally Carter

quote: There are some things your mind has been hiding from you.
author: Obert Skye,  Leven Thumps and the Gateway to Foo

quote: We must not think of the things we could do with, but only of the things that we can't do without.
author: Jerome K. Jerome,  Three Men in a Boat

quote: I believe that we do not know anything for certain, but everything probably.
author: Christiaan Huygens,  Oeuvres Completes

quote: What comes, when it comes, will be what it is.
author: Alberto Caeiro,  The Collected Poems of Alberto Caeiro

quote: Sometimes we can focus so much on nothing that we make it a big something of nothing
author: Ricky Maye,  An Emerging Spirituality
